1
00:00:04,129 --> 00:00:05,380
(BEEPS)

2
00:00:05,631 --> 00:00:06,965
Sontar-Ha!

3
00:00:07,591 --> 00:00:10,844
Strategic Intelligence Update 427.

4
00:00:10,928 --> 00:00:13,222
Subject, the Doctor.

5
00:00:13,347 --> 00:00:15,432
Commander Strax reporting.

6
00:00:15,974 --> 00:00:17,684
Strax, what are you doing?

7
00:00:17,893 --> 00:00:20,145
This ship is about to crash
into the heart of London.

8
00:00:21,188 --> 00:00:22,981
Reporting to Sontar.

9
00:00:23,649 --> 00:00:26,693
I have acquired vital
tactical information

10
00:00:26,777 --> 00:00:30,489
-which could change the course...
-By the Goddess, are you blogging?

11
00:00:30,656 --> 00:00:33,283
I resent your attitude
to my status updates.

12
00:00:33,367 --> 00:00:36,912
Millions of innocent people are going
to be vaporised in 12 minutes!

13
00:00:37,287 --> 00:00:40,415
Exactly. I've got to pass
the time somehow.

14
00:00:40,499 --> 00:00:41,625
(SIGHS)

15
00:00:41,792 --> 00:00:44,253
Come on, Jenny! Work to do!

16
00:00:47,172 --> 00:00:48,632
Men!

17
00:00:51,843 --> 00:00:54,972
The Time Lord known as the Doctor.

18
00:00:55,222 --> 00:00:57,683
Sontaran enemy number one.

19
00:00:57,975 --> 00:00:59,351
(RUMBLING)

20
00:00:59,685 --> 00:01:02,938
There are many myths and legends
concerning the Doctor,

21
00:01:03,021 --> 00:01:05,607
and principal among them
is his secret ability

22
00:01:05,691 --> 00:01:07,609
to change appearance.

23
00:01:08,110 --> 00:01:10,445
This is the First Doctor,

24
00:01:10,821 --> 00:01:12,656
designated Doctor number one.

25
00:01:13,073 --> 00:01:16,910
Although the numbering
does get a little trickier later on.

26
00:01:17,452 --> 00:01:18,620
As you can see,

27
00:01:18,704 --> 00:01:21,248
this Doctor is a woman,

28
00:01:21,665 --> 00:01:24,334
a delusional crone
with unpleasant trousers

29
00:01:24,418 --> 00:01:27,629
and unrealistic hair.

30
00:01:28,005 --> 00:01:30,507
The Doctor is able,
when damaged or injured,

31
00:01:30,591 --> 00:01:32,968
to renew his physical form.

32
00:01:33,218 --> 00:01:36,680
This is a process
known as deterioration.

33
00:01:38,432 --> 00:01:42,352
Faced with certain death
after an encounter with the Cybermen,

34
00:01:42,436 --> 00:01:44,605
the First Doctor
was forced to regenerate

35
00:01:44,688 --> 00:01:47,441
into a new and younger form.

36
00:01:47,649 --> 00:01:48,859
This process...

37
00:01:50,402 --> 00:01:51,653
failed.

38
00:01:51,862 --> 00:01:54,406
This Doctor, Doctor number two,

39
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:58,243
was captured by his own people
and sentenced to a fate

40
00:01:58,327 --> 00:01:59,911
worse than death.

41
00:02:01,705 --> 00:02:05,917
The Third Doctor,
a strange and tragic hybrid,

42
00:02:06,335 --> 00:02:08,712
half man, half granny,

43
00:02:09,046 --> 00:02:12,174
was forced to regenerate
because he was frightened

44
00:02:12,257 --> 00:02:14,760
-by a big spider.
-(SCREECHES)

45
00:02:15,218 --> 00:02:17,721
The Fourth Doctor was no improvement

46
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:22,643
and took to wearing a giant sheep frond

47
00:02:23,101 --> 00:02:27,481
to lend himself color and personality.
Unsuccessfully.

48
00:02:29,983 --> 00:02:33,779
The Fifth Doctor showed some grasp
of the military virtue of camouflage

49
00:02:34,112 --> 00:02:36,782
by having no distinguishing
features whatsoever.

50
00:02:37,074 --> 00:02:39,076
Following events
on the planet Androzani,

51
00:02:39,284 --> 00:02:40,911
this Doctor was unavoidably...

52
00:02:41,828 --> 00:02:42,913
inflated.

53
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:45,374
The Sixth Doctor
showed significantly less

54
00:02:45,457 --> 00:02:47,334
-understanding of camouflage...
-(RUMBLING)

55
00:02:47,417 --> 00:02:50,754
...and died during his single attempt
at physical exercise.

56
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:54,549
The Sixth Doctor's regeneration
into his seventh form

57
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:57,803
brings us to a great
and terrible mystery.

58
00:02:58,804 --> 00:03:00,931
What happened to the rest of him?

59
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:03,642
Where is all the leftover Doctor?

60
00:03:04,851 --> 00:03:06,812
Stored somewhere, perhaps?

61
00:03:07,312 --> 00:03:09,606
In secret vats?

62
00:03:10,273 --> 00:03:14,486
Beware, fellow Sontarans,
there may be more of him out there.

63
00:03:16,488 --> 00:03:19,700
The Eighth Doctor added
a new dimension to his persona,

64
00:03:19,950 --> 00:03:23,203
undreamt of by his
previous incarnations.

65
00:03:24,371 --> 00:03:25,455
(SIGHS)

66
00:03:26,206 --> 00:03:27,624
Puberty.

67
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:33,088
These new activities
and the attendant lifestyle

68
00:03:33,171 --> 00:03:35,507
had an inevitable consequence.

69
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:38,301
The War Doctor.

70
00:03:39,803 --> 00:03:43,724
The only Doctor with any potential
for being any good at all.

71
00:03:44,391 --> 00:03:46,685
Sadly, however, he was rubbish.

72
00:03:46,977 --> 00:03:48,395
(EXPLOSION)

73
00:03:48,687 --> 00:03:52,023
Despite promising tendencies
towards death and destruction,

74
00:03:52,816 --> 00:03:56,153
when it came to the pleas
of the suffering and dying,

75
00:03:56,987 --> 00:04:00,198
the Doctor was once again all ears.

76
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:02,826
(STRAX SNICKERS)

77
00:04:04,411 --> 00:04:05,829
All ears!

78
00:04:06,329 --> 00:04:08,206
(LAUGHS)

79
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:10,625
Sorry.

80
00:04:10,709 --> 00:04:12,753
A bit of human humor for you there.

81
00:04:12,836 --> 00:04:14,671
(LAUGHING)

82
00:04:16,214 --> 00:04:17,549
All ears!

83
00:04:19,843 --> 00:04:22,053
After another kissing incident,

84
00:04:22,179 --> 00:04:25,223
this Doctor liked girls so much
he decided to become one.

85
00:04:25,515 --> 00:04:29,227
The Tenth Doctor was on a voyage
of discovery, self-improvement

86
00:04:29,770 --> 00:04:31,021
and personal development

87
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:34,858
that led to his regeneration into
the Tenth Doctor.

88
00:04:35,358 --> 00:04:37,569
He just didn't want to go!

89
00:04:37,861 --> 00:04:39,404
What was he so afraid of?

90
00:04:39,905 --> 00:04:41,364
The Eleventh Doctor.

91
00:04:42,532 --> 00:04:45,702
Or possibly the Twelfth.
Technically the Thirteenth.

92
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:47,788
Who can say?

93
00:04:48,205 --> 00:04:51,082
By now the Doctor had learned
to take it all on the chin.

94
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:53,376
(EXPLOSION)

95
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:55,921
Chin.

96
00:04:57,798 --> 00:04:59,633
I didn't even mean that one.

97
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,051
(LAUGHING)

98
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:05,639
Why's that funny? That isn't even funny.
(LAUGHING)

99
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:10,727
Why am I laughing?
What's funny about chins?

100
00:05:11,269 --> 00:05:12,896
(STRAX LAUGHING)

101
00:05:13,939 --> 00:05:16,733
Stop it. Stop all the chins.

102
00:05:17,901 --> 00:05:19,736
It's not funny!

103
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:22,072
(LAUGHING)

104
00:05:27,744 --> 00:05:29,830
Be warned, fellow Sontarans,

105
00:05:29,913 --> 00:05:32,457
word has reached us
on all sub-space channels,

106
00:05:32,582 --> 00:05:35,752
a new incarnation
of the Doctor is imminent.

107
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:38,797
Information is scarce at this point,

108
00:05:38,922 --> 00:05:41,967
-but early indications suggest...
-Strax, with me, now.

109
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:44,010
We must get to London immediately!

110
00:05:44,094 --> 00:05:45,929
But I thought we were going?

111
00:05:46,179 --> 00:05:49,516
Oh, no, we've fixed
the engines, it's fine.

112
00:05:49,599 --> 00:05:51,601
But we've just had a message
from Scotland Yard.

113
00:05:51,768 --> 00:05:55,438
Apparently, there's something
impossible in the Thames.

114
00:05:59,651 --> 00:06:00,819
(BEEPS)

